WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.107
Brothers and sisters, the message of
today's Gospel that we heard revolves

00:00:05.107 --> 00:00:07.661
around two themes: humility and pride.

00:00:07.661 --> 00:00:13.620
I believe we all struggle with these
weaknesses and sins, because each of us

00:00:13.620 --> 00:00:21.281
wants to be first, each of us wants to
be in the top position, each of us wants

00:00:21.281 --> 00:00:27.240
to show off, and this is somehow always
more pronounced in humans than humility.

00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:31.292
Humility can best be seen in many saints.

00:00:31.292 --> 00:00:36.282
However, to understand today's gospel
or this comparison between humility

00:00:36.282 --> 00:00:42.769
and pride, we need to look at two
images from the Holy Scriptures.

00:00:42.769 --> 00:00:51.252
If we go to the book of Genesis, chapter
three, we will see Adam who became proud,

00:00:51.252 --> 00:00:59.735
who took a place that did not belong to
him, because he wanted to be like God.

00:01:00.055 --> 00:01:04.056
Therefore, he wanted to
essentially decide to be God.

00:01:04.056 --> 00:01:11.171
And immediately we see that he took the
first place which was not meant for him.

00:01:11.171 --> 00:01:18.729
That is why the master casts him out,
and we know that he was cast out and

00:01:18.729 --> 00:01:21.842
realized that he was naked and nothing.

00:01:21.842 --> 00:01:28.067
However, the second image that can help
us, the positive one, is Jesus himself.

00:01:28.067 --> 00:01:35.181
In one place in the Holy Scripture, it
says, "He, being in the form of God,

00:01:35.181 --> 00:01:40.517
did not consider equality with God
something to be grasped, but emptied

00:01:40.517 --> 00:01:43.630
himself, taking the form of a servant."

00:01:44.550 --> 00:01:52.047
So Jesus who comes, the Son of God, who
deserves the first place, renounces it.

00:01:52.047 --> 00:01:58.545
He renounces it and takes the last
place, takes the cross on which,

00:01:58.545 --> 00:02:04.044
like Adam, he is stripped, naked,
spat upon, mocked, and betrayed.

00:02:04.044 --> 00:02:11.042
Here, brothers and sisters, from these
two images, we can see for ourselves which

00:02:11.042 --> 00:02:19.540
path we should take, which place we want
to be in, and what we want to achieve.

00:02:20.150 --> 00:02:28.527
Do we really want to be the ones who always
impose themselves first, who are full of

00:02:28.527 --> 00:02:35.427
themselves, who only believe in themselves,
or do we want to follow Jesus' example?

00:02:35.427 --> 00:02:41.341
These two images not only show
us the path we should take.

00:02:41.341 --> 00:02:47.747
Did you listen carefully to the first
reading from the Book of Sirach?

00:02:47.747 --> 00:02:55.140
There, we all receive the code, the
guidance, on which path to take and how.

00:02:55.660 --> 00:03:01.707
So, you probably didn't notice, so I'll
read that sentence again, and it says,

00:03:01.707 --> 00:03:08.619
when a father advises his son on what
to do, he tells him this: the greater

00:03:08.619 --> 00:03:12.074
you are, the more humble you should be.

00:03:12.074 --> 00:03:16.394
The greater you are, the
more humble you should be.

00:03:16.394 --> 00:03:22.873
Tonight, when you get a chance, that's
the third chapter of the Book of Sirach,

00:03:22.873 --> 00:03:25.033
write that sentence down somewhere.

00:03:25.033 --> 00:03:33.673
It's not a problem to be great, it's not a
problem to be someone, but it is a problem if

00:03:33.673 --> 00:03:36.265
that great someone doesn't humble themselves.

00:03:37.245 --> 00:03:39.955
You have so many wonderful
successful people—scientists,

00:03:39.955 --> 00:03:43.053
artists, businesspeople—who are,
as they say, great individuals.

00:03:43.053 --> 00:03:49.636
I don't know if you've had the opportunity
to talk to such people, but the greater they

00:03:49.636 --> 00:03:52.733
are, the more humble and simple they are.

00:03:52.733 --> 00:03:56.993
Sometimes, in conversations with
these people, we are surprised when we

00:03:56.993 --> 00:04:02.414
know who they are and what they have
achieved, and when you approach them,

00:04:02.414 --> 00:04:05.125
you see that they are truly humble.

00:04:05.160 --> 00:04:11.373
And that's why Sirach says, the greater you
are, the more you should humble yourself.

00:04:11.373 --> 00:04:14.272
It's not a problem to be great.

00:04:14.272 --> 00:04:21.314
The problem is if you are arrogant and
if you want to be something you are not.

00:04:21.314 --> 00:04:23.800
So, what is the issue here?

00:04:23.800 --> 00:04:28.770
The issue is how we measure our
greatness, our worth, and what

00:04:28.770 --> 00:04:31.256
place we think we should take.

00:04:31.256 --> 00:04:34.155
Should we become arrogant
or humble ourselves?

00:04:34.155 --> 00:04:39.955
That's why Sirach warns, the greater you
are, the more you should humble yourself.

00:04:40.475 --> 00:04:44.718
We see this many times in the Holy Scripture.

00:04:44.718 --> 00:04:50.377
When Mary experienced the Annunciation
and proclaimed her Magnificat, there is a

00:04:50.377 --> 00:04:56.978
sentence where she says, "He has brought
down the mighty from their thrones and

00:04:56.978 --> 00:05:03.108
exalted those of humble estate." Those
who are humble will always be rewarded.

00:05:03.108 --> 00:05:06.408
And there is no worry in that.

00:05:06.408 --> 00:05:12.538
If you are going through something
like Jesus on the cross, who humbled

00:05:12.538 --> 00:05:19.140
himself, gave up the first place, and
took the last place, God exalted him.

00:05:19.560 --> 00:05:21.643
Where did He place Him?

00:05:21.643 --> 00:05:23.309
At His right hand.

00:05:23.309 --> 00:05:24.976
At His right hand.

00:05:24.976 --> 00:05:29.975
So we too, brothers and sisters,
sometimes struggle a lot, worrying about

00:05:29.975 --> 00:05:32.475
ourselves, but let God be glorified.

00:05:32.475 --> 00:05:39.141
If we are humble, God will turn everything
for the good and place us where we

00:05:39.141 --> 00:05:44.557
need to be, along with our plans,
projects, ideas, and even our lives.

00:05:44.557 --> 00:05:49.140
If you are humble, there
is room for God to work.

00:05:49.620 --> 00:05:54.042
But we make the biggest mistakes when we
are arrogant and make decisions on our own.

00:05:54.042 --> 00:05:57.359
And where do we see this
and how do we see it?

00:06:00.190 --> 00:06:04.745
A little while ago, I said this
sentence: the greater you are,

00:06:04.745 --> 00:06:07.023
the more humble you should be.

00:06:07.023 --> 00:06:12.717
And the one who knows they are great—do
you think Jesus didn't know his greatness?

00:06:12.717 --> 00:06:17.652
Yet, knowing his greatness, he humbled
himself, took up the cross, and went

00:06:17.652 --> 00:06:20.310
through everything he needed to go through.

00:06:21.250 --> 00:06:24.803
Why wasn't that a problem for Jesus?

00:06:24.803 --> 00:06:26.833
Because he was self-aware.

00:06:26.833 --> 00:06:32.416
He knew his worth, who
he was, and what he was.

00:06:32.416 --> 00:06:36.985
Do you know who gets the most arrogant today?

00:06:36.985 --> 00:06:41.045
It's not the narcissistic
people who are tall.

00:06:41.045 --> 00:06:47.136
The problematic narcissistic individuals
aren't the big ones, but the empty ones.

00:06:47.136 --> 00:06:47.644
Why?

00:06:47.644 --> 00:06:50.690
Because a narcissistic person is empty.

00:06:51.860 --> 00:06:57.487
That's why they constantly seek applause,
why they want to be in first place, why

00:06:57.487 --> 00:07:00.488
they always strive for some kind of success.

00:07:00.488 --> 00:07:00.863
Why?

00:07:00.863 --> 00:07:05.365
Because if they face opposition, it
means they've lost their foundation, and

00:07:05.365 --> 00:07:10.617
you keep validating them with applause,
pushing them to the top, because they lack

00:07:10.617 --> 00:07:16.244
inner confidence in who they are, what
kind of person they are, and their worth.

00:07:16.244 --> 00:07:18.120
And that's why narcissistic people...

00:07:18.300 --> 00:07:23.793
They constantly need to be in first place,
constantly need praise, because as soon as

00:07:23.793 --> 00:07:26.723
it's not like that, they go into crisis.

00:07:26.723 --> 00:07:28.188
They need our validation.

00:07:28.188 --> 00:07:31.118
They will do anything just to be praised.

00:07:31.118 --> 00:07:35.879
And then you see, my dears, how
easy it is to understand this.

00:07:35.879 --> 00:07:40.640
So, a narcissistic and arrogant person
is often someone who is conceited and

00:07:40.640 --> 00:07:43.570
empty, who knows they are not worth much.

00:07:43.570 --> 00:07:46.500
And they are afraid of
that within themselves.

00:07:46.500 --> 00:07:52.009
However, we Christians do not
evaluate ourselves based on who can

00:07:52.009 --> 00:07:58.520
define our worth if we were to look
through the lens of psychology.

00:07:58.520 --> 00:08:04.530
Instead, we see through different eyes,
spiritual ones, and that is Jesus.

00:08:04.530 --> 00:08:06.534
He is our measure.

00:08:06.534 --> 00:08:14.548
If His life, which was invaluable, was
freely given to die on the cross for us,

00:08:14.548 --> 00:08:18.555
then you see what makes our lives valuable.

00:08:18.555 --> 00:08:19.733
Through Jesus' sacrifice.

00:08:19.733 --> 00:08:22.090
See how much we are worth.

00:08:22.090 --> 00:08:26.412
Sometimes it seems easy to say
that we were dearly bought.

00:08:26.412 --> 00:08:30.733
This means we have dignity
because we are children of God.

00:08:30.733 --> 00:08:36.626
And we are worth as much as we are
worth before God and nothing more.

00:08:36.626 --> 00:08:42.912
None of us here is worth more because of
our abilities, having a doctorate, owning a

00:08:42.912 --> 00:08:46.055
company, or being successful in this or that.

00:08:46.055 --> 00:08:46.419
No.

00:08:46.419 --> 00:08:51.519
Each of us is worth only as
much as we are worth before God.

00:08:51.519 --> 00:08:53.705
Saint Francis knew this very well.

00:08:53.705 --> 00:08:57.712
We are worth as much as
we are worth before God.

00:08:57.712 --> 00:09:01.355
Therefore, we have no right
to be arrogant or prideful.

00:09:01.355 --> 00:09:01.720
Why?

00:09:01.720 --> 00:09:05.727
What do you have that you
did not receive from God?

00:09:05.727 --> 00:09:12.285
Even if you have some ability or are good
at something, it is all a gift from God.

00:09:12.785 --> 00:09:19.839
But in this way, you can become so proud
that you fall away from your Creator who

00:09:19.839 --> 00:09:23.574
made you that way or gave you that gift.

00:09:23.574 --> 00:09:23.989
Why?

00:09:23.989 --> 00:09:26.895
Sometimes we obstruct the logic of salvation.

00:09:26.895 --> 00:09:33.119
As I just said, when we are not humble,
God cannot do anything through us.

00:09:33.119 --> 00:09:38.514
If you have those talents or some
abilities or whatever, they are given

00:09:38.514 --> 00:09:41.834
to you to multiply, to make use of.

00:09:42.314 --> 00:09:43.426
Remember those talents.

00:09:43.426 --> 00:09:48.245
So, why boast that you're good
at this or that, when you know

00:09:48.245 --> 00:09:50.839
everything is given to you by God?

00:09:50.839 --> 00:09:56.028
And it's given to you for the building
up of the church, your family,

00:09:56.028 --> 00:09:57.881
your community, or anything else.

00:09:57.881 --> 00:10:01.216
In the end, where can we see this best?

00:10:01.216 --> 00:10:03.811
We have all come to this table.

00:10:03.811 --> 00:10:09.000
That's why I always say how important
this table is, not the doors below.

00:10:09.839 --> 00:10:15.253
So, because the Eucharist takes place
here, the living Jesus is made present.

00:10:15.253 --> 00:10:18.168
And who has Jesus invited here today?

00:10:18.168 --> 00:10:23.581
In this church, no one deserves
either the first or the last place.

00:10:23.581 --> 00:10:29.411
There is a beautiful saying by a
saint, I can't remember who said it.

00:10:29.411 --> 00:10:34.825
None of you are so holy that you
should stay outside the church.

00:10:35.645 --> 00:10:41.193
None of you are so sinful outside
the church that you cannot enter it.

00:10:41.193 --> 00:10:43.968
Because Jesus has called all of us.

00:10:43.968 --> 00:10:47.535
He has invited all of us to His feast.

00:10:47.535 --> 00:10:50.309
And that is the most beautiful thing.

00:10:50.309 --> 00:10:53.480
There is no first, second, or third place.

00:10:53.480 --> 00:10:59.822
We are all equal, and if we are even
a little humble, we will realize that

00:10:59.822 --> 00:11:06.956
we are sinful and that it is a gift
to be able to be around His table, to

00:11:06.956 --> 00:11:12.108
partake in Him, even though we are still
flawed, still sinning, still falling.

00:11:12.108 --> 00:11:19.639
But we know that Jesus has invited all of
us to the Lamb's feast and to awaken in us

00:11:19.639 --> 00:11:25.981
that desire to be humble and to long for
that living city, the living church, the

00:11:25.981 --> 00:11:31.530
glorified Jerusalem, as the Holy Scripture
says, so that we can all participate there.

00:11:32.130 --> 00:11:37.095
That is why, brothers and sisters,
humility is important to us.

00:11:37.095 --> 00:11:42.060
Have you ever thought about
how casually we come to church?

00:11:42.060 --> 00:11:47.025
We receive communion, partake
in the body and blood of Christ.

00:11:47.025 --> 00:11:50.636
Do we ever think, do I deserve this?

00:11:50.636 --> 00:11:52.442
It is a gift.

00:11:52.442 --> 00:12:00.115
Am I worthy enough to be proud before God,
thinking I am holy or good or something?

00:12:00.115 --> 00:12:06.435
Attributing to ourselves perhaps some mild
or small, I don't know, values or merits.

00:12:08.295 --> 00:12:14.932
No matter how weak we are, whenever
we look at Jesus and His humility,

00:12:14.932 --> 00:12:17.302
we too should reflect that.

00:12:17.302 --> 00:12:24.887
A Christian cannot be humble, give up the
first places and glory, and leave behind what

00:12:24.887 --> 00:12:32.947
is said, "the greater you are, the more you
should humble yourself," if they do not have

00:12:32.947 --> 00:12:35.317
a well-developed relationship with Jesus.

00:12:35.317 --> 00:12:39.584
The first fruit of such a
relationship is gratitude.

00:12:39.584 --> 00:12:46.695
I don't know about your feelings, but
sometimes when I confess, I come out of

00:12:46.695 --> 00:12:54.755
the confessional, and I just want to kneel
before the cross, bow my head, and not move.

00:12:54.875 --> 00:13:00.340
Because, as you might say, you are
in a state of gratitude because you

00:13:00.340 --> 00:13:05.415
can't believe that God has shown
you love and mercy again, washed you

00:13:05.415 --> 00:13:07.757
clean again, brought you back again.

00:13:07.757 --> 00:13:13.613
I always say this, whether in church or
anywhere else, we can observe one another.

00:13:13.613 --> 00:13:17.907
It's beautiful when you see
someone who is grateful to God

00:13:17.907 --> 00:13:20.249
and aware of their own weaknesses.

00:13:20.249 --> 00:13:20.640
Why?

00:13:20.920 --> 00:13:23.837
When a person doesn't get puffed up.

00:13:23.837 --> 00:13:26.338
When a person isn't so arrogant.

00:13:26.338 --> 00:13:28.839
Last Sunday, I preached about this.

00:13:28.839 --> 00:13:30.506
He focuses on himself.

00:13:30.506 --> 00:13:35.924
And brother, whenever any of us starts
focusing on ourselves and looks honestly

00:13:35.924 --> 00:13:39.259
in the mirror, we might start to cry.

00:13:39.259 --> 00:13:43.843
But precisely that, encountering
the truth, is held by God's love.

00:13:43.843 --> 00:13:47.595
No matter how bad I am, God loves me.

00:13:47.595 --> 00:13:49.824
He will pull me out.

00:13:49.824 --> 00:13:51.608
He will renew me.

00:13:51.608 --> 00:13:53.837
That's when humility comes in.

00:13:53.837 --> 00:13:59.634
Remember the prodigal son when he
says, "Oh, I came to my senses."

00:13:59.634 --> 00:14:06.323
How beautiful it is to see those new
converts when they come to their senses.

00:14:06.323 --> 00:14:11.674
Those constant tears, that continuous
gratitude to God for finding them at

00:14:11.674 --> 00:14:14.350
any stage of life, it's beautiful.

00:14:14.690 --> 00:14:16.224
That is God's grace.

00:14:16.224 --> 00:14:19.676
Here, brothers and everyone,
that's why we are called.

00:14:19.676 --> 00:14:24.279
That humility is not just a
mantra, nor should it be fake.

00:14:24.279 --> 00:14:30.801
I'm sorry to say, but my people, there
is a lot of false humility in the church.

00:14:30.801 --> 00:14:33.869
A learned pattern for
humility is not humility.

00:14:33.869 --> 00:14:37.705
What I told you, looking like
this, that's not humility.

00:14:37.705 --> 00:14:43.459
Thank God for your gestures and everything,
but by the fruits of the Holy Spirit,

00:14:43.459 --> 00:14:46.145
by the fruits of the Holy Spirit.

00:14:46.425 --> 00:14:51.491
For example, I can look like an angel
in church, but then on the steps or

00:14:51.491 --> 00:14:53.708
in the parking lot, I attack someone.

00:14:53.708 --> 00:14:57.824
Haven't I told you many times how
often I've seen arguments in the

00:14:57.824 --> 00:14:59.724
confession line on St. Anthony's day?

00:15:02.345 --> 00:15:06.011
And everyone humbly stands in line
for confession with their rosaries,

00:15:06.011 --> 00:15:08.345
but God forbid you take their spot.

00:15:08.645 --> 00:15:13.145
Oh, but then you see the
fire ignite from within.

00:15:13.145 --> 00:15:16.746
Is that the fruit of the Holy Spirit?

00:15:16.746 --> 00:15:20.347
The fruit of the Holy Spirit is peace.

00:15:20.347 --> 00:15:23.948
The fruit of the Holy Spirit is patience.

00:15:23.948 --> 00:15:25.748
Okay, it's not right.

00:15:25.748 --> 00:15:27.999
Someone got ahead of you.

00:15:27.999 --> 00:15:30.249
Someone took something from you.

00:15:30.249 --> 00:15:33.400
Someone deceived you,
humiliated you, offended you.

00:15:33.400 --> 00:15:35.200
How do we react?

00:15:35.200 --> 00:15:37.451
What flares up inside us?

00:15:37.451 --> 00:15:45.102
What we can learn from Jesus, let them
be free, what we can learn from Jesus is

00:15:45.102 --> 00:15:50.954
precisely that He remained silent, that
He endured, that He bore it, knowing

00:15:50.954 --> 00:15:55.454
that He did it out of pure love for us.

00:15:55.474 --> 00:16:01.092
And one of the great aspects of
Jesus' humility is precisely that.

00:16:01.092 --> 00:16:07.645
He knew the value of His life,
yet He still gave it for us.

00:16:07.645 --> 00:16:11.858
Jesus gave His life to us, knowing its worth.

00:16:11.858 --> 00:16:18.411
We, as Christian believers and people,
if we know our own worth, are also

00:16:18.411 --> 00:16:21.219
called to give ourselves to others.

00:16:21.219 --> 00:16:26.368
In any way, each in their own
state, mission, or calling.

00:16:26.368 --> 00:16:33.390
But the meaning of our lives, if we
are aware of how valuable we are.

00:16:33.390 --> 00:16:39.350
What we can do, as the Scripture and the
prophet Sirach say, is humble ourselves

00:16:39.350 --> 00:16:44.912
and do something for God and for others,
and not just think about ourselves.

00:16:44.912 --> 00:16:45.310
Amen.

